      • getDynamicFrameSlotValueType

        CFrame getDynamicFrameSlotValueType(CFrame superType,
                                    java.util.List<CFrame> subTypes)
        Retrieves a CFrame object to be used as a value-type for a frame-valued slot. The returned frame will have the specified super-frame and sub-frame types, will have no associated slots or default slot-values, and will be CFrame.hidden(). If no such frame has been previously generated via this method then it will be dynamically created with an auto-generated name based on that of the super-frame.
        Parameters:
        superType - Super-type for slot value-type frame
        subTypes - sub-types for slot value-type frame
        Returns:
        Required slot value-type frame
